[Ep07]

4
00:02:00,360 --> 00:02:01,120
These are

5
00:02:01,120 --> 00:02:03,240
some of the designs I've done in recent years.

6
00:02:03,240 --> 00:02:05,760
Our design plan this time is mainly about

7
00:02:06,440 --> 00:02:08,120
the combination of tradition and modernity.

8
00:02:08,120 --> 00:02:09,479
This is my previous design

9
00:02:09,479 --> 00:02:11,720
themed by space and time.

10
00:02:12,440 --> 00:02:14,640
It's full of plagiarisms.

11
00:02:17,560 --> 00:02:18,160
How is it going?

12
00:02:19,720 --> 00:02:21,240
Not well.

13
00:02:21,880 --> 00:02:22,840
I have met five people

14
00:02:22,920 --> 00:02:24,000
in the past two days.

15
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:25,720
None is qualified.

16
00:02:25,720 --> 00:02:26,520
Too expensive?

17
00:02:27,040 --> 00:02:28,040
It's not about money.

18
00:02:29,840 --> 00:02:32,160
Their designs are all so tacky

19
00:02:32,200 --> 00:02:33,240
and expensive as hell.

20
00:02:34,520 --> 00:02:36,000
In such matters,

21
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:37,000
my idea is

22
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:38,880
to first recognize their design philosophy,

23
00:02:38,880 --> 00:02:40,920
and spend as little as possible.

24
00:02:40,920 --> 00:02:41,600
Am I right?

25
00:02:41,600 --> 00:02:42,400
Huh?

26
00:02:42,840 --> 00:02:43,280
Yeah.

27
00:02:52,800 --> 00:02:53,440
Xiaoyu.

28
00:02:54,079 --> 00:02:54,880
Didn’t you say that

29
00:02:54,880 --> 00:02:57,040
you know someone who does interior design?

30
00:02:57,280 --> 00:02:58,160
Did you find him?

31
00:02:59,040 --> 00:03:00,280
He replied to me that

32
00:03:00,280 --> 00:03:01,360
he is on a case right now.

33
00:03:02,760 --> 00:03:05,920
There is no conflict. He can take this job.

34
00:03:06,160 --> 00:03:08,160
He is very professional.

35
00:03:08,600 --> 00:03:10,960
He must finish the case before taking the next one.

36
00:03:11,160 --> 00:03:12,560
Unlike some designers,

37
00:03:12,920 --> 00:03:14,280
who take the order anyway

38
00:03:14,520 --> 00:03:15,760
just for the money.

39
00:03:17,040 --> 00:03:18,240
The way you describe him

40
00:03:18,440 --> 00:03:20,200
really interests me.

41
00:03:21,200 --> 00:03:22,200
How did you two meet?

42
00:03:24,200 --> 00:03:25,920
He was my roommate’s boyfriend

43
00:03:25,920 --> 00:03:27,440
when I was studying in Norway.

44
00:03:27,560 --> 00:03:29,079
He came back to China after graduation.

45
00:03:30,160 --> 00:03:31,160
Where's your roommate?

46
00:03:31,560 --> 00:03:32,600
She's still in Norway.

47
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:35,120
Did they break up?

48
00:03:35,520 --> 00:03:36,000
Yeah.

49
00:03:38,880 --> 00:03:40,280
I have to meet this guy.

50
00:03:41,720 --> 00:03:42,320
Set up a meeting.

51
00:03:43,400 --> 00:03:43,840
Got it.

52
00:04:00,640 --> 00:04:01,240
Shanshan.

53
00:04:02,360 --> 00:04:03,760
Why are you giving me a gift again?

54
00:04:03,960 --> 00:04:05,320
My friends, a couple,

55
00:04:05,320 --> 00:04:07,040
rented a greenhouse in the suburbs.

56
00:04:07,040 --> 00:04:08,560
These are the strawberries they grow.

57
00:04:08,560 --> 00:04:10,280
No pesticides are used.

58
00:04:10,600 --> 00:04:11,720
They gave me two boxes.

59
00:04:11,720 --> 00:04:12,520
I can't eat that many.

60
00:04:12,520 --> 00:04:13,760
So I want to give you some.

61
00:04:14,240 --> 00:04:15,040
Come whenever you like.

62
00:04:15,040 --> 00:04:16,399
But don't bring anything next time.

63
00:04:16,399 --> 00:04:17,160
OK?

64
00:04:17,160 --> 00:04:18,360
Of course not.

65
00:04:19,040 --> 00:04:19,800
Is tea okay?

66
00:04:19,800 --> 00:04:20,279
Sure.

67
00:04:20,720 --> 00:04:21,760
Are you writing?

68
00:04:21,880 --> 00:04:22,440
Yeah.

69
00:04:22,880 --> 00:04:24,040
Whenever I can.

70
00:04:24,880 --> 00:04:25,560
Do you

71
00:04:25,800 --> 00:04:27,040
do this every day?

72
00:04:27,920 --> 00:04:28,400
Ummm...

73
00:04:28,840 --> 00:04:30,280
You won't have time to write

74
00:04:30,280 --> 00:04:31,400
when the kid comes home, right?

75
00:04:32,080 --> 00:04:33,760
I can have a longer time

76
00:04:33,760 --> 00:04:35,200
when my child and husband are asleep.

77
00:04:35,640 --> 00:04:37,240
Can you live like that every day?

78
00:04:38,360 --> 00:04:39,200
What can I do?

79
00:04:39,280 --> 00:04:40,240
Be careful. It's hot.

80
00:04:41,360 --> 00:04:42,360
Is it okay

81
00:04:42,960 --> 00:04:44,800
for your husband to sleep alone

82
00:04:44,800 --> 00:04:46,159
every day?

83
00:04:46,280 --> 00:04:47,280
Haven't you heard that?

84
00:04:47,480 --> 00:04:49,360
The standard configuration

85
00:04:49,360 --> 00:04:50,400
of a mature and stable family,

86
00:04:50,400 --> 00:04:52,240
is a perfect gentleman

87
00:04:52,240 --> 00:04:54,320
and a woman who can't be turned on.

88
00:04:54,600 --> 00:04:56,040
People talk about the seven-year itch.

89
00:04:56,520 --> 00:04:58,120
We have been married for almost nine years.

90
00:04:58,159 --> 00:04:59,640
We would feel awkward

91
00:04:59,760 --> 00:05:00,800
holding hands on a whim.

92
00:05:02,920 --> 00:05:04,360
Well.

93
00:05:04,960 --> 00:05:06,680
Everything about your married life

94
00:05:06,680 --> 00:05:07,920
is new to me,

95
00:05:08,400 --> 00:05:09,920
as if I had never been married.

96
00:05:10,400 --> 00:05:12,520
When did you start being like this?

97
00:05:12,760 --> 00:05:14,930
From the moment you went to the toilet
 with the door open,

98
00:05:14,930 --> 00:05:17,040
and he came in calmly and shaved in front of the mirror,

99
00:05:17,280 --> 00:05:19,280
your love has been sublimated.

100
00:05:20,720 --> 00:05:22,280
Are you two

101
00:05:22,480 --> 00:05:23,360
not in love anymore?

102
00:05:23,480 --> 00:05:24,520
We are good friends,

103
00:05:24,520 --> 00:05:25,520
so don't break my heart,

104
00:05:25,520 --> 00:05:26,160
OK?

105
00:05:26,360 --> 00:05:26,800
OK.

106
00:05:28,880 --> 00:05:31,360
I have evolved from a passionate wife

107
00:05:31,360 --> 00:05:33,640
to an indifferent middle-aged woman.

108
00:05:33,960 --> 00:05:35,240
My husband takes half of the credit,

109
00:05:35,240 --> 00:05:36,680
and my child takes another half.

110
00:05:37,120 --> 00:05:37,760
You have a child too.

111
00:05:37,760 --> 00:05:38,880
You don't need me to tell you that.

112
00:05:38,880 --> 00:05:39,560
Um.

113
00:05:40,040 --> 00:05:41,520
The husband who enters marriage

114
00:05:41,520 --> 00:05:43,840
will degenerate into a name very soon.

115
00:05:44,080 --> 00:05:45,320
For seven days a week,

116
00:05:45,320 --> 00:05:47,000
he has to work for five days.

117
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:48,240
Because of his business,

118
00:05:48,240 --> 00:05:50,120
he has to socialize from time to time.

119
00:05:50,600 --> 00:05:51,920
Even if he’s at home on weekends,

120
00:05:51,920 --> 00:05:54,080
he’s not really at home.

121
00:05:55,480 --> 00:05:56,760
Before the advent of social media,

122
00:05:56,760 --> 00:05:58,800
he used to lie on the sofa watching videos.

123
00:05:59,120 --> 00:06:01,160
He first watched the full set of Discovery.

124
00:06:01,320 --> 00:06:02,440
From volcanic eruption

125
00:06:02,440 --> 00:06:03,840
to gorilla growth.

126
00:06:04,160 --> 00:06:05,160
Later he started watching

127
00:06:05,160 --> 00:06:06,440
war documentaries.

128
00:06:06,600 --> 00:06:07,920
From the World War I

129
00:06:07,920 --> 00:06:09,320
to the Libyan War.

130
00:06:09,680 --> 00:06:11,160
After having a smartphone,

131
00:06:11,440 --> 00:06:13,560
he started to play games and scroll down Twitter.

132
00:06:13,560 --> 00:06:15,160
He has no time to communicate with me

133
00:06:15,160 --> 00:06:17,560
on the emotional level.

134
00:06:23,600 --> 00:06:25,680
Enough about me.

135
00:06:25,680 --> 00:06:27,080
Why did you come here?

136
00:06:27,360 --> 00:06:28,840
Just to deliver strawberries?

137
00:06:28,920 --> 00:06:29,520
I

138
00:06:29,520 --> 00:06:31,600
am here to bring you medicine.

139
00:06:33,720 --> 00:06:34,440
What medicine?

140
00:06:34,600 --> 00:06:36,480
The medicine for your complaint.

141
00:06:39,040 --> 00:06:40,240
Let's come straight to the point.

142
00:06:40,240 --> 00:06:41,600
I want to open a restaurant.

143
00:06:41,600 --> 00:06:43,200
It's already open, to be precise.

144
00:06:43,400 --> 00:06:44,480
I want to get you in.

145
00:06:44,480 --> 00:06:45,400
300,000 RMB.

146
00:06:45,400 --> 00:06:46,560
10% of the shares.

147
00:06:46,560 --> 00:06:47,240
In or out?

148
00:06:50,520 --> 00:06:51,520
Huh? Huh? Huh?

149
00:06:51,520 --> 00:06:53,800
Is that the only word you can say?

150
00:06:55,120 --> 00:06:56,360
This is a bit sudden.

151
00:06:56,960 --> 00:06:59,720
What event in life didn't happen suddenly?

152
00:06:59,880 --> 00:07:01,320
Now this restaurant,

153
00:07:01,320 --> 00:07:01,760
including me,

154
00:07:01,760 --> 00:07:02,880
has four shareholders.

155
00:07:02,880 --> 00:07:04,040
You can be the fifth.

156
00:07:04,440 --> 00:07:06,160
Consider it a nice distraction,

157
00:07:06,320 --> 00:07:08,480
so you don’t have to 
face your husband and child every day

158
00:07:08,480 --> 00:07:10,240
and enter menopause early.

159
00:07:20,720 --> 00:07:22,040
But this is huge,

160
00:07:22,320 --> 00:07:23,760
I need to discuss this with my husband.

161
00:07:24,320 --> 00:07:25,760
Look at you.

162
00:07:26,200 --> 00:07:26,800
All right.

163
00:07:26,800 --> 00:07:28,280
Take your time.

164
00:07:28,280 --> 00:07:29,600
I'll keep this position for you anyway.

165
00:07:29,600 --> 00:07:30,680
I'm busy. Gotta go.

166
00:07:30,920 --> 00:07:31,320
Tell me

167
00:07:31,520 --> 00:07:32,520
when you make up your mind.

168
00:07:32,520 --> 00:07:33,000
OK.

169
00:07:33,280 --> 00:07:34,440
You are leaving now?

170
00:07:34,440 --> 00:07:34,960
Yeah.

171
00:07:34,960 --> 00:07:36,080
Not stay for dinner?

172
00:07:36,080 --> 00:07:36,680
Nope.

173
00:07:37,680 --> 00:07:38,120
OK.

174
00:07:38,240 --> 00:07:39,000
Take care.

175
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:39,600
Bye-bye.

176
00:07:50,800 --> 00:07:51,480
Sorry.

177
00:07:51,680 --> 00:07:53,080
It's so hard to drive in the alleys.

178
00:07:53,320 --> 00:07:53,520
Come on.

179
00:07:53,640 --> 00:07:54,240
Hop on.

180
00:07:56,159 --> 00:07:57,600
Long time no see.

181
00:07:57,760 --> 00:07:59,240
Why don't you stay in Norway

182
00:07:59,240 --> 00:08:00,320
but come back to Beijing?

183
00:08:00,320 --> 00:08:01,280
I'm back for you.

184
00:08:01,280 --> 00:08:02,000
Cut it out.

185
00:08:02,000 --> 00:08:03,240
Buckle up.

186
00:08:17,200 --> 00:08:18,200
How long it's been since we last met?

187
00:08:21,920 --> 00:08:23,120
About five or six years?

188
00:08:24,280 --> 00:08:26,240
Why haven't you changed a bit?

189
00:08:26,920 --> 00:08:27,920
You haven't, either.

190
00:08:31,360 --> 00:08:33,320
Have you finished your case?

191
00:08:33,840 --> 00:08:35,240
Almost finished.

192
00:08:35,840 --> 00:08:36,960
That's great.

193
00:08:47,400 --> 00:08:48,400
How do you feel?

194
00:08:49,080 --> 00:08:49,880
The layout is not bad.

195
00:08:50,400 --> 00:08:51,240
Then what do you say?

196
00:08:52,000 --> 00:08:52,680
Some time ago,

197
00:08:52,680 --> 00:08:54,320
I just finished designing a theme restaurant.

198
00:08:54,520 --> 00:08:55,560
I can show you my work.

199
00:08:56,080 --> 00:08:56,960
If you are interested in

200
00:08:56,960 --> 00:08:58,440
our design philosophy,

201
00:08:58,560 --> 00:08:59,400
we can talk about it.

202
00:09:00,040 --> 00:09:00,760
Let's do it now.

203
00:09:04,440 --> 00:09:05,200
Follow me.

204
00:09:05,200 --> 00:09:05,920
OK.

205
00:09:08,000 --> 00:09:09,160
Do you think it'll work?

206
00:09:09,160 --> 00:09:10,080
Good first impression.

207
00:09:10,080 --> 00:09:11,240
But I don't know about his capacity.

208
00:09:11,240 --> 00:09:12,340
Let's take a look at his works.

209
00:09:12,720 --> 00:09:13,720
Follow that yellow car.

210
00:09:17,040 --> 00:09:18,440
When designing this restaurant,

211
00:09:18,440 --> 00:09:20,480
I used the concept of space folding.

212
00:09:20,960 --> 00:09:22,280
I restructured the arch elements

213
00:09:22,280 --> 00:09:24,440
in classical architecture,

214
00:09:24,800 --> 00:09:26,840
and incorporated them 
into contemporary aesthetics.

215
00:09:26,840 --> 00:09:28,600
I want to blur the boundary

216
00:09:28,600 --> 00:09:29,840
between the wall and the roof.

217
00:09:30,240 --> 00:09:32,340
So I winded the wall

218
00:09:32,400 --> 00:09:34,160
and extended it into the ceiling.

219
00:09:34,160 --> 00:09:36,000
I used a tailor-like technique

220
00:09:36,280 --> 00:09:37,360
to attach the copper material

221
00:09:37,360 --> 00:09:38,680
to the curved surface.

222
00:09:39,680 --> 00:09:40,400
For the key vision,

223
00:09:40,400 --> 00:09:42,200
I used glass with western classical colors,

224
00:09:42,520 --> 00:09:45,280
so as to bring a surreal experience to the diners

225
00:09:47,320 --> 00:09:49,440
I used silk noodles for the table cloth.

226
00:09:49,960 --> 00:09:50,680
Its reflection

227
00:09:50,680 --> 00:09:53,160
echoes the color of copper.

228
00:09:54,240 --> 00:09:55,840
Do you also design the tablecloth?

229
00:09:55,840 --> 00:09:56,560
Of course.

230
00:09:56,560 --> 00:09:57,720
Including tableware.

231
00:09:58,720 --> 00:10:00,800
If you just eat to fill your stomachs,

232
00:10:00,800 --> 00:10:02,120
then why do you decorate?

233
00:10:02,120 --> 00:10:03,520
Splashing water to sweep the floor,

234
00:10:03,520 --> 00:10:05,160
setting up a few tables and chairs

235
00:10:05,160 --> 00:10:06,200
like hole-in-the-wall places.

236
00:10:08,680 --> 00:10:10,400
Do you want that kind of restaurant?

237
00:10:11,560 --> 00:10:12,320
Then you don’t need to

238
00:10:12,320 --> 00:10:14,320
spend the money to hire a designer.

239
00:10:16,920 --> 00:10:18,080
In my opinion,

240
00:10:18,080 --> 00:10:20,120
Restaurants are not only to fill our stomachs,

241
00:10:20,520 --> 00:10:21,840
but also to socialize.

242
00:10:22,440 --> 00:10:23,760
An all-rounded design,

243
00:10:24,200 --> 00:10:25,280
including details,

244
00:10:25,480 --> 00:10:27,040
as long as it is related to aesthetics,

245
00:10:27,040 --> 00:10:27,800
I'll be in charge.

246
00:10:29,120 --> 00:10:30,280
What do you think?

247
00:10:30,280 --> 00:10:32,280
I think it's so cool.

248
00:10:32,280 --> 00:10:33,480
Beautiful.

249
00:10:34,360 --> 00:10:35,280
See?

250
00:10:35,280 --> 00:10:37,800
This space echoes your aesthetics.

251
00:10:40,880 --> 00:10:42,400
But I think...

252
00:10:42,400 --> 00:10:43,760
Here...

253
00:10:43,760 --> 00:10:44,600
You think it's bad?

254
00:10:44,600 --> 00:10:45,440
No. No.

255
00:10:45,440 --> 00:10:46,920
It's terrific.

256
00:10:47,280 --> 00:10:48,720
But...

257
00:10:48,720 --> 00:10:49,920
It's okay, just tell me.

258
00:10:51,000 --> 00:10:52,560
How much is the average cost here?

259
00:10:52,560 --> 00:10:53,200
500 RMB.

260
00:10:53,880 --> 00:10:55,320
That's awkward.

261
00:10:55,320 --> 00:10:57,520
500 RMB is not too much,

262
00:10:57,520 --> 00:10:59,400
but ordinary people can’t afford it.

263
00:10:59,400 --> 00:11:00,480
Isn't it kind of light luxury?

264
00:11:01,120 --> 00:11:01,760
And also.

265
00:11:02,080 --> 00:11:02,760
Look.

266
00:11:02,760 --> 00:11:03,720
These places

267
00:11:03,720 --> 00:11:05,120
can obviously be used to set up tables,

268
00:11:05,120 --> 00:11:06,480
but you placed decorations instead.

269
00:11:06,480 --> 00:11:08,280
This virtually limits the number of diners

270
00:11:08,280 --> 00:11:09,320
and reduces the turnover.

271
00:11:14,360 --> 00:11:15,240
You are right.

272
00:11:16,200 --> 00:11:17,870
I want to ask you that

273
00:11:17,870 --> 00:11:19,920
would you come here to eat?

274
00:11:22,400 --> 00:11:23,400
I'm afraid not.

275
00:11:24,560 --> 00:11:25,560
Let's put it this way.

276
00:11:25,560 --> 00:11:26,800
If I want to entertain

277
00:11:26,800 --> 00:11:28,200
important clients,

278
00:11:28,480 --> 00:11:30,240
I will choose a more magnificent place,

279
00:11:30,240 --> 00:11:32,640
because that kind of banquet does not have a budget.

280
00:11:32,640 --> 00:11:34,040
But if I have a gathering with friends,

281
00:11:34,200 --> 00:11:35,560
I won’t consider the decoration.

282
00:11:35,560 --> 00:11:36,560
I would only focus on

283
00:11:36,560 --> 00:11:37,680
how good the food is.

284
00:11:42,640 --> 00:11:43,720
Sorry.

285
00:11:43,720 --> 00:11:44,640
We are not professional.

286
00:11:44,640 --> 00:11:45,680
Please don't mind.

287
00:11:46,520 --> 00:11:47,640
Whatever a client says,

288
00:11:47,640 --> 00:11:49,360
it's not about being professional or not.

289
00:11:49,760 --> 00:11:50,960
It's about their needs.

290
00:11:51,800 --> 00:11:52,680
To be frank,

291
00:11:52,680 --> 00:11:54,280
it's about what kind of people

292
00:11:54,280 --> 00:11:55,560
are their target customers.

293
00:11:58,120 --> 00:11:59,040
